{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of finance |nativename = ''Ministarstvo finansija'' |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = 1879 |preceding1 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of Montenegro]] |headquarters = Stanka Dragojevića 2, Podgorica |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name= Darko Radunović |minister1_pfo = |minister2_name= |minister2_pfo = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |website = [https://www.mf.gov.me/ mf.gov.me] |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Finance in the [[Government of Montenegro|Government]] of [[Montenegro]]''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]:Ministarstvo finansija u Vladi Crne Gore, '''MFVCG''') is the ministry in the [[Government of Montenegro]] which is in charge of the nation's finances. The ministry was established in 1879 as a ministry of the [[Principality of Montenegro]]. It was abolished in late 1922, but restored 23 years later, in 1945.
