{{Infobox windmill | name = Xarolla Windmill | image = Xarolla Windmill 2016.jpeg | image_size = 300px | caption = Xarolla Windmill | name_of_mill = | location_of_mill = | coordinates = {{Coord|35|49|54.5|N|14|28|50.5|E|type:landmark_region:MT|display=inline,title}} | operator = | built = 1724 | purpose = [[grist mill|Corn mill]] | type = [[Tower mill]] | storeys = | base_storeys = | roundhouse_storeys = | smock_sides = | sail_number = Six sails | sail_type = [[Common sails]] | windshaft = | winding = | fantail_blades = | auxpower = | pairs_of_millstones = | stone_size = | saw_type = | pump_type = | scoop_dia = | lost = | other = }} The '''Xarolla Windmill''' at [[Żurrieq]], [[Malta]] is [[List of windmills in Malta|one of the windmills]] constructed by the [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of St. John]] in the villages and towns of Malta. It was built in the 18th-century and is presently one of the most preserved [[List of windmills in Malta|windmills in Malta]]. The windmill is an agri-tourism attraction and is found in a complex of agricultural buildings such as a farmhouse, a chapel, catacombs<ref name="auto">DOI (24 February 2005). [http://www.doi-archived.gov.mt/EN/press_releases/2005/02/pr0282.asp ''WIRJA PERMANENTI DWAR L-IMTIEĦEN TAR-RIĦ '']. Department of Information (DOI), [[Valletta]], [[Malta]]. Press release no. 0282. Retrieved 18 June 2026.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20151004/life-features/time-to-get-those-walking-boots-on.586974|title=Time to get those walking boots on|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=}}</ref> and others. The windmill is also used as an art studio.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20140907/arts-entertainment/Artistic-anarchy-in-Bubaqra.534856|title=Artistic anarchy in Bubaqra|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=}}</ref>
In 1674 [[Grand Master (order)|Grand Master]] [[Nicolas Cotoner]] built five windmills around Malta, one of which was tax-Xarolla. Tax-Xarolla Windmill was built by Grand Master [[Antonio Manoel de Vilhena]] in 1724. Sometimes after 1998, this was restored to its original working order. It is now the only functioning windmill on the islands of Malta.<ref name="auto"/> This is a valuable witness of local culture and heritage; it still has parts of the original mechanisms and can still grain the wheat. In the year 2000, this building was passed over to be administered by the Żurrieq Local Council and is intended to serve also as a cultural centre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.windmillsofmalta.nl/db.cgi?p=detail;r=12#details|title=Windmills of malta - Xarolla Windmill|website=www.windmillsofmalta.nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zurrieqparish.org/node/441|title=Account Suspended|website=www.zurrieqparish.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20130630/arts-entertainment/Xarolla-Windmill-to-serve-as-base-for-artistic-project.476216|title=Xarolla Windmill to serve as base for artistic project|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20090305/local/xarolla-windmill-extensively-damaged.247537|title=Xarolla windmill extensively damaged|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maltatoday.com.mt/arts/art/48942/art_off_the_mainstream_grid__ryan_falzon|title=Art off the mainstream grid - Ryan Falzon|publisher=}}</ref>
